						<summary>

						<p>On the west face of the south pillar in the rock-cut shrīne in the Mēlaikōvil temple.</p>						

						<p>This damaged Chōḷa inscription records the gift of 5 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold by Śāttam Piḍāri for feeding the <hi rend="italic">Panmāhēśvaras</hi> of the temple of Tirumēṟṟaḷi-mādēva in Tirunilakkuṉṟam in Kuṉṟiyūr0nāḍu.</p>						

